    {
      "id": "3c97cdb3-4b50-46d6-a53a-7397c2ac8e3e",
      "type": "description",
      "value": {
        "latex": "On considère l'équation $(E)~:~(z-1)^n-(z+1)^n=0$ où $n$ est un entier naturel supérieur ou\négal à $2$ donné.",
        "html": "<p>On considère l’équation <span class=\"math inline\">\\((E)~:~(z-1)^n-(z+1)^n=0\\)</span> où <span class=\"math inline\">\\(n\\)</span> est un entier naturel supérieur ou égal à <span class=\"math inline\">\\(2\\)</span> donné.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "1ba62328-e1c6-4060-ae1c-33ed78b0cda1",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer que les solutions de $(E)$ sont imaginaires pures.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer que les solutions de <span class=\"math inline\">\\((E)\\)</span> sont imaginaires pures.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "c8dc0d9d-9154-4441-84c6-1c5cacfd41ca",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soit $z\\in\\Cc$. Soient $M$, $A$ et $B$ les points d'affixes resectives $z$, $1$ et $-1$.\n\n$$\\begin{align*}\nz\\;\\mbox{solution\nde}\\;(E)&\\Rightarrow(z-1)^n=(z+1)^n\\Rightarrow|(z-1)^n|=|(z+1)^n|\\Rightarrow|z-1|^n=|z+1|^n\n\\Rightarrow|z-1|=|z+1|\\\\\n &\\Rightarrow AM=BM\\Rightarrow M\\in\\mbox{med}[AB]\\Rightarrow M\\in(Oy)\\Rightarrow z\\in i\\Rr.\n\\end{align*}$$",
        "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(z\\in\\Cc\\)</span>. Soient <span class=\"math inline\">\\(M\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(A\\)</span> et <span class=\"math inline\">\\(B\\)</span> les points d’affixes resectives <span class=\"math inline\">\\(z\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(1\\)</span> et <span class=\"math inline\">\\(-1\\)</span>.</p>\n<p><span class=\"math display\">\\[\\begin{align*}\nz\\;\\mbox{solution\nde}\\;(E)&amp;\\Rightarrow(z-1)^n=(z+1)^n\\Rightarrow|(z-1)^n|=|(z+1)^n|\\Rightarrow|z-1|^n=|z+1|^n\n\\Rightarrow|z-1|=|z+1|\\\\\n &amp;\\Rightarrow AM=BM\\Rightarrow M\\in\\mbox{med}[AB]\\Rightarrow M\\in(Oy)\\Rightarrow z\\in i\\Rr.\n\\end{align*}\\]</span></p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "bc523cbe-c247-410a-9a75-beae126ecada",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer que les solutions de $(E)$ sont deux à deux opposées.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer que les solutions de <span class=\"math inline\">\\((E)\\)</span> sont deux à deux opposées.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "f749fe71-d69c-44aa-bde6-57f055aee479",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soit $z\\in\\Cc$.\n\n$$(-z-1)^n-(-z+1)^n=(-1)^n((z+1)^n-(z-1)^n)=-(-1)^n((z-1)^n-(z+1)^n).$$\nPar suite,\n\n$$z\\;\\mbox{solution de}\\;(E)\\Leftrightarrow(z-1)^n-(z+1)^n=0\\Leftrightarrow(-z-1)^n-(-z+1)^n=0\\Leftrightarrow-z\\;\\mbox{solution de}\\;(E).$$",
        "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(z\\in\\Cc\\)</span>.</p>\n<p><span class=\"math display\">\\[(-z-1)^n-(-z+1)^n=(-1)^n((z+1)^n-(z-1)^n)=-(-1)^n((z-1)^n-(z+1)^n).\\]</span> Par suite,</p>\n<p><span class=\"math display\">\\[z\\;\\mbox{solution de}\\;(E)\\Leftrightarrow(z-1)^n-(z+1)^n=0\\Leftrightarrow(-z-1)^n-(-z+1)^n=0\\Leftrightarrow-z\\;\\mbox{solution de}\\;(E).\\]</span></p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "e0c7cdf2-8f97-4964-b6c3-0e8b13638a4e",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Résoudre $(E)$.",
        "html": "<p>Résoudre <span class=\"math inline\">\\((E)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "7d29219d-9879-48c2-ab11-33a2721a3aec",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soit $z\\in\\Cc$.\n$$\\begin{align*}\nz\\;\\mbox{solution de}\\;(E)&\\Leftrightarrow(z-1)^n=(z+1)^n\\Leftrightarrow\\exists k\\in\\llbracket0,n-1\\rrbracket/\\;z-1=e^{2ik\\pi/n}(z+1)\\\\\n&\\Leftrightarrow\\exists k\\in\\llbracket1,n-1\\rrbracket/\\;z=-\\frac{e^{2ik\\pi/n}+1}{e^{2ik\\pi/n}-1}\n\\Leftrightarrow\\exists k\\in\\llbracket1,n-1\\rrbracket/\\;z=-\\frac{e^{ik\\pi/n}+e^{-ik\\pi/n}}{e^{ik\\pi/n}-e^{-ik\\pi/n}}\\\\\n&\\Leftrightarrow\\exists k\\in\\llbracket1,n-1\\rrbracket/\\;z=-\\frac{2\\cos\\frac{k\\pi}{n}}{2i\\sin\\frac{k\\pi}{n}}\n\\Leftrightarrow\\exists k\\in\\llbracket1,n-1\\rrbracket/\\;z=i\\cotan\\frac{k\\pi}{n}\n\\end{align*}$$",
        "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(z\\in\\Cc\\)</span>. <span class=\"math display\">\\[\\begin{align*}\nz\\;\\mbox{solution de}\\;(E)&amp;\\Leftrightarrow(z-1)^n=(z+1)^n\\Leftrightarrow\\exists k\\in\\llbracket0,n-1\\rrbracket/\\;z-1=e^{2ik\\pi/n}(z+1)\\\\\n&amp;\\Leftrightarrow\\exists k\\in\\llbracket1,n-1\\rrbracket/\\;z=-\\frac{e^{2ik\\pi/n}+1}{e^{2ik\\pi/n}-1}\n\\Leftrightarrow\\exists k\\in\\llbracket1,n-1\\rrbracket/\\;z=-\\frac{e^{ik\\pi/n}+e^{-ik\\pi/n}}{e^{ik\\pi/n}-e^{-ik\\pi/n}}\\\\\n&amp;\\Leftrightarrow\\exists k\\in\\llbracket1,n-1\\rrbracket/\\;z=-\\frac{2\\cos\\frac{k\\pi}{n}}{2i\\sin\\frac{k\\pi}{n}}\n\\Leftrightarrow\\exists k\\in\\llbracket1,n-1\\rrbracket/\\;z=i\\cotan\\frac{k\\pi}{n}\n\\end{align*}\\]</span></p>\n"
      }
    }
  ]
